To make SeaLion Agent work behind proxy. Follow following steps
1. Login as root
2. Enter into /usr/local/sealion-agent/etc/config directory
3. Create a file with name "proxy.json" and copy-paste following lines with <proxy-url> changed to your proxy address

{
    "http_proxy" : "<proxy-url>"
}


SeaLion uses node.js v0.8.18. Source code of which is available at http://nodejs.org/dist/v0.8.18/node-v0.8.18.tar.gz